entry.def: You describe people or things as nameless when you do not know their name or when they do not have a name.

example.ex: They can have their cases rejected, without reasons being given, by nameless officials.
example.tran: 他们的诉求可能会被一些不知姓名的官员们莫名其妙地驳回。

entry.tran: 不宜说出名字（或名称）的
entry.def: If you say that someone or something will remain nameless, you mean that you will not mention their name, often because you do not want to embarrass them.

example.ex: A local friend who shall be nameless warned me that I was in for trouble soon.
example.tran: 一个不便说出其名的当地朋友警告我，我不久肯定会有麻烦。
